.0-M1 artifact is self-contained apart from scala-library 2.13.18 and com.typesafe:config 1.4.5, and meaningful classic ActorSystem/Props/dispatch/serialization coverage is reachable without Docker, service dependencies, or extra Maven dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No extra environment variables or system properties are required for ordinary classic actor coverage. Avoid the removed deprecated org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor/TypedProps/TypedActorExtension APIs that caused the existing Scala compilation failure. If retaining DNS-settings coverage that touches JDK internal DNS APIs, keep JVM/native args exporting java.base/sun.net.dns to unnamed modules.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Pekko 2.0.0-M1 removed a lot of deprecated APIs, including the TypedActor-style APIs used by the current 1.1.5 tests; the fix is test/API migration, not an added dependency.\",\n    \"pekko-actor-typed_2.13 is a separate module for the new typed actor API; adding it would test another artifact and is not required for core pekko-actor coverage.\",\n    \"Pekko 2.0.0-M1 is a milestone release with Java 17+ baseline, so local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ba0276c6776df18016a4268374b6c8194ab132246c71c56cb\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4488, "output": 1352, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39120, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782736928772, "responseId": "resp_0ba0276c6776df18016a42682154248194bfd99e5979a03d26"}}
